==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la}} {{term|aberratus|aberrātus|lang=la}}, perfect passive participle of {{term|aberro|aberrō|wander, stray or deviate from|lang=la}}, formed from {{term|ab||from, away from|lang=la}} + {{term|erro|errō|stray|lang=la}}.

===Verb===
{{en-verb|aberrat|ing}}

# {{intransitive}} To [[go astray]]; to [[diverge]]; to [[deviate]] (from).
#: ''Their own defective and '''aberrating''' vision.'' - De Quincey
# {{transitive}} To [[distort]]; to cause [[aberration]] of.

